Package br.com.armange.commons.thread.async

Class AbstractTryAsyncBuilder<T extends AbstractTryAsyncBuilder<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • br.com.armange.commons.thread.async.AbstractTryAsyncBuilder<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CallableTryAsyncBuilder, MappedResourcesTryAsyncBuilder, ResourcesTryAsyncBuilder, ResourceTryAsyncBuilder, RunnableTryAsyncBuilder
    public abstract class AbstractTryAsyncBuilder<T extends AbstractTryAsyncBuilder<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstraction to implement a try-async operations builder. These operations are simply try-catch-finally statements executed on a new thread.
    Since:
    2020-06-22 V1.1.0 (JDK 1.8)

      • execute

        protected void execute​(RunnableWithException attemptedExecution)
        Executes a thread according to the given implementation, which simulates a try block, configured with an (or more) exception catcher, as well as a finalizer. As with a try-catch block implementation, only the main implementation(try-block) is mandatory.
        Parameters:
        attemptedExecution - the thread implementation, which simulates the try-block
        See Also:
        addCatcher(java.lang.Class<? extends java.lang.Throwable>, java.util.function.Consumer<java.lang.Throwable>), finallyAsync(java.lang.Runnable)

      • execute

        protected <S> void execute​(java.util.concurrent.Callable<S> task,
                           java.util.function.Consumer<S> resultConsumer)
        A new thread will be configured and executed with the following structure:

        In addition to the thread implementation, existing exception handling implementations will be added, however, only the implementation corresponding to the thrown exception will be executed. After the thread runs, even if it throws an exception, the finalizing implementation (if configured) will be executed. Finally, if the thread produces some object as a result, and if there is a consumer for that result, it will be executed.
        Type Parameters:
        S - the type of the object resulting from the execution of the thread.
        Parameters:
        task - the thread implementation, which simulates the try-block
        resultConsumer - the thread result consumer implementation.
        See Also:
        addCatcher(java.lang.Class<? extends java.lang.Throwable>, java.util.function.Consumer<java.lang.Throwable>), finallyAsync(java.lang.Runnable)

      • consumeExceptionIfExists

        protected java.util.function.Consumer<java.lang.Throwable> consumeExceptionIfExists()
        It consumes an exception according the given consumers added by addCatcher(java.lang.Class<? extends java.lang.Throwable>, java.util.function.Consumer<java.lang.Throwable>). If no consumers is present, no action will be performed. Only consumers compatible with the exception will be triggered. It will be triggered twice if the exception consumer is rethrowing any exception. The second calling will be triggered in "java.lang.Thread#dispatchUncaughtException(Throwable)". see "AbstractThreadBuilder#getThreadFactory()"
        Returns:
        the exception consumer implementation.

      • execute

        public abstract void execute()
        As a try-block implementation, performs the thread configured with the exception catcher(s) and a finalizer. If the thread generates a result value and no exceptions is thrown, a result consumer will be triggered.
        See Also:
        execute(RunnableWithException), execute(Callable, Consumer)
